column2: 1. Gross government investment consists of general government and government enterprise expenditures for fixed assets; inventory

column3: investment is included in government consumption expenditures.

column2: 2. Consumption expenditures for durable goods excludes expenditures classified as investment, except for goods transferred to

column3: foreign countries by the Federal Government.

column2: 3. Compensation of government employees engaged in new own-account investment and related expenditures for goods and services

column3: are classified as investment in structures and in software.  The
compensation of all general government employees is shown in the addenda.

column2: 4. Consumption of fixed capital, or depreciation, is included in government consumption expenditures as a partial measure of the

column3: value of the services of general government fixed assets; use of
depreciation assumes a zero net return on these assets.

column2: 5. Beginning with 2001, in accordance with the Consolidated Appropriations Act of 2001, includes compensation of employees of

column3: Indian tribal governments reclassified from the private sector.
